We can start by writing $f(x)$ as

\begin{align*}
f(x) &= \cot \frac{x}{4} - \cot x \\
&= \frac{\cos \frac{x}{4}}{\sin \frac{x}{4}} - \frac{\cos x}{\sin x} \\
&= \frac{\cos \frac{x}{4} \sin x - \cos x \sin \frac{x}{4}}{\sin \frac{x}{4} \sin x}.
\end{align*}

Using the angle subtraction formula for sine, we get

\begin{align*}
\cos \frac{x}{4} \sin x - \cos x \sin \frac{x}{4} &= \sin (x - \frac{x}{4}) \\
&= \sin \left( \frac{4x}{4} - \frac{x}{4} \right) \\
&= \sin \left( \frac{3x}{4} \right).
\end{align*}

So we have

\begin{align*}
f(x) &= \frac{\sin \frac{3x}{4}}{\sin \frac{x}{4} \sin x}.
\end{align*}

Comparing this expression to the given expression, we can see that $k = \boxed{\frac{3}{4}}.$
